<br>
I found this really helpful for me - I use old quake-style mouselook controllers.  Mapping backstab to Delete and evade to End upped my damage output a good amount over using the silly number keys.  This makes it easy for me to land backstabs on casting mobs even when  I solo. <p><BR><br><B><I><img src="http://www.druidmail.com/santerre2.gif">Santerre.</I></B></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=elegance>Elegance</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/13/02 12:33:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12988.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How to remap backstab to a key?</span><hr size=1> I only wish it was possible to map keys without setting them as one of the &quot;skill&quot; keys first. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/urulan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rulan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www3.sympatico.ca/headleya/rulan_icon.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/13/02 12:38:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12988.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www3.sympatico.ca/headleya/rulan_60x60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How to remap backstab to a key?</span><hr size=1> I use space bar.. my thumb rests there naturally when I use Quake style movement keys. <p><h6><a hr